---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="Methodology notes for the TorchLens Model Menagerie preview.">
  <section class="shell max-w-4xl space-y-8 py-10">
    <div>
      <p class="mono text-sm" style="color: var(--accent);">Methodology</p>
      <h1 class="mt-2 text-4xl font-semibold">Every diagram starts from one line of TorchLens</h1>
      <p class="mt-4 leading-8" style="color: var(--secondary);">Phase 0 publishes the real rendered diagram gallery through the final catalog schema. The production atlas will fill in source, validation, licensing, and tlspec metadata without changing the data shape.</p>
    </div>
    <section class="panel p-5">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Credibility model</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 leading-7" style="color: var(--secondary);">The funnel distinguishes catalog presence, rendered diagrams, and forward validation. In this preview, forward validation is intentionally zero because render coverage is the only verified predicate.</p>
    </section>
    <section class="panel p-5">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Reproducibility</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 leading-7" style="color: var(--secondary);">The generated export is deterministic and content-addressed. All pages read through src/lib/catalog.ts, so a future pipeline export can replace the manifest scrape at that single data seam.</p>
    </section>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
